Rating: 4
WOW. 4 ingredients and incredibly easy prep--I was not expecting these to be so phenomenal! I did add a tiny dash of vanilla to the batter but other than that made these as written. Some reviewers skipped the sugar dipping but DON'T!! Somehow it transforms these cookies into an almost tart-tasting perfect mouth-melting piece of crumbly, buttery, hazelnutty perfection. I took them out of the oven about 10 minutes ago and I think I already ate 5!

Rating: 3
This recipe was really delicious...however a little too sweet for me. I recommend using just flour to dust batter before freezing. Like a previous reviewer, my food processor was broken, so I used my blender and pulsed ingredients. It worked fine until I added the butter. I transferred everything into a bowl and 'cut-up' the mixture in a criss-cross pattern. The mixture turned out perfectly! This recipe is great with other nuts as well! Enjoy.

