Rating: 4
Excellent and easy. I've made these several times and they're always a hit. Light, crumbly, buttery and full of the flavor of the nuts (they'd probably be good with other toasted nuts too). Stuck them in the freezer for half an hour and they were solid enough to bake. I found they need about 5 minutes after they come out of the oven before you dip in sugar, otherwise they crumble really easily.

